assets.name: Ukrainian war - 1
assets.description: This is a piece of a digital art, generated by Discoperi (https://discoperi.com). Between 2016 and 2022 Discoperi has built thousands of neural networks and selected the best for this effort. The neural network was fed by all available photos and videos available online on Russia-Ukraine war, started on 24th of February 2022. This is a part of a collection "War in Ukraine. Early days" which consists of the materials for the first week of the war.

collection.description:
In 1937 Picasso created one of his monumental paintings Guernica. It showed a horror, violence and chaos of Nazi Germany attacking Basque country. The great author expressed all the shouts and screams, tears and hopes, missing dreams and last breaths of people, animals and nature of the village. 85 years later, the experience of seeing the painting is still mentally heavy for an average person. Unfortunately the history has repeated again. 
On 24th of February 2022 Russia has invaded Ukraine. Russian president Putin wanted to reunite USSR and aimed to take over Ukrainians as a nation, their uniqueness and freedom - two qualities of free country. Putin's army targeted civilians. Quite the parallel to Hitler's attack expressed in Guernica.
As a reaction to this brutal act, Discoperi has created a unique neural network, which was fed by all the photos and videos of the early days of the war. The collection you see now is an output of this AI-led process. This is how AI sees the war.
collection.name: War in Ukraine. Early days

collection.description:
The magical world of the fairy from the constellation of the Big Dog. Junia arrived on earth from the planet Yu. Where everything is like on earth, only instead of people, "animals are people" on two legs, but they also have pets. 
10 years old, a virtuoso graphic artist, she creates a drawing in a few minutes, immediately draws with a liner, without first using a pencil and an eraser. Junia has been drawing her world since May 2014, when the baby was only 2.5 years old. Parents carefully keep the entire archive, more than 15,000 drawings.
An individual author's style has been created. Each drawing carries a heartfelt story. In this kind world, animals live in absolute harmony, there are not only dogs, but also other animals, mice, cats, elephants, birds, dinosaurs... 
The first collection of NFT will feature 5555 archival works of an early age. The earlier the drawing was created, the higher the price. The range is from 9 years with 0.05 etn, to 2.5 years the price starts from 1 etn.

Responsibly or recklessly.

Drug Receipts is a defense of nuance. It is a prescription against polarization. Become a pusher of deeper and more thoughtful content. Trade in illicit conversations. Join the growing legion of Drug Snugglers and help spread Drug Receipts’ unique brand of mind-altering substance.

assets.description:
The Sozoro Collection is an art project by artist Takayuki Yokoyama.

Sozoro is a Japanese term that describes the emotions we experience without reason. The same kanji in sozoro is also in the word for manga,the popular Japanese art form. Manga literally translates to “whimsical pictures”-an apt description of Hokusai Katsushika’s collection of sketches“Hokusai Manga”

This Collection is about continually creating work in the limited peaceful time available. It is not bound by any ideology or message. Instead,He created these pieces in a manner that can be described as sozoro; out of all the things he had seen or imagined, he simply depicted whatever he felt like depicting.

All works are limited to a maximum of 5 per theme. Each piece includes a serial number & signature. A special feature of this NST is that only buyers will be provided with a DL link to Hi-resolution data for 16:9(3840x2160px)digital display.

Su D. Oku Saves Earth! is an NFT Collection of 25,000 increasingly difficult sudoku puzzles separated into volumes and chapters.

Saga 1! - 40 volumes: Easy

Saga 2! - 40 volumes: Medium

Saga 3! - 40 volumes: Hard

#SAGA 5! - 5 VOLUMES: EXTREME!


Each difficulty is distinguished by a unique background pattern, and the answer keys and instructions on how to play can be found hosted [here](https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1PWKFsqmDxMdK6WZ8GTwXha_DHg7eor5P?usp=sharing)!

Each Volume follows our hero, Su D. Oku as he criss-crosses time, space, the world and even the galaxy to save planet Earth. 

But this is not just a story, with each NFT, 90% of royalties and initial sales go towards fusion research like [ITER](https://www.iter.org/) and [Wendelstein 7-X](https://www.ipp.mpg.de/w7x), which is helping to save the planet from a climate change crisis through fusion energy. The same type of energy that powers the Sun! Help Su D. Oku Save Earth. Today!
collection.name: Su D. Oku Saves Earth!

The Rare Bears are your ticket into the BearVerse with the most vibrant community around.
